This introductory course deals with the changing role of information in a changing society and explains the importance and meaning of information management.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to provide overview about the changing role of the information in the society as well as about socio-economic and socio-cultural developments.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course, students: - will understand the role and meaning of information in modern society; - have overview about the social developments related to information diffusion; - know specific features and challenges of modern information society; - will understand the structural factors which direct the individual behavior in information society.
